{
    "attributes": {
        "action": "Require AUTOMATIC by election if an MP changes party during a term of office",
        "additional_details": "The reason is that since the electorate voted that MP in as a representative of that party, if they stood for one.",
        "background": "A petition to recall an MP is opened in three situations and a by-election forced so long as 10% of the electorate sign such a petition. However, if an MP changes party during a term of office there is nothing the constituents can do. We think there should be an automatic by election.",
